id: pm-f58e
title: Fix slow/oversized local vector snapshot and mislabeled search fallback
description: "Two search subsystem fixes. (1) PERF: persistLanceDbLocalTable serialized the local vector snapshot with JSON.stringify(obj,null,2) — pretty-printing put every embedding float on its own indented line, ~doubling file size and parse/serialize cost on every mutation and semantic query. Switched to compact JSON (internal, gitignored cache; JSON.parse is whitespace-agnostic). Measured dev-repo snapshot 33MB->19MB, stringify 195ms->98ms. (2) CORRECTNESS: undici (Node fetch) collapses connection errors to 'fetch failed' with the real code on error.cause.code, so a downed Ollama was mislabeled 'error' instead of 'connection' in semantic fallback warnings. Now walks the cause chain. Also corrected the inaccurate 'Mutations do not auto-embed by default' stale-index warning copy."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: bug,perf,search,vector-store
created_at: "2026-05-30T21:43:26.240Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-30T21:43:43.376Z"
author: maintainer-agent
acceptance_criteria: Snapshot serialized compactly; downed-backend fallback labeled connection; warning copy accurate
resolution: "Fixed: compact local snapshot + accurate connection-class fallback labeling."
close_reason: "Compact snapshot in vector-stores.ts persistLanceDbLocalTable (33MB->19MB, stringify 195->98ms); cause-chain classifier in search.ts + corrected stale-index warning. Tests: vector-store-adapter.spec (compact assertion), search-command.spec all green."
